// Spec note: `state_definition` (`lang.ebnf §7` line 334) appears in the
// grammar both as a `module_item` (`§5` line 188) and — per the 2016
// tutorial NS17 example reproduced in `§6` lines 254–262 — as an item
// of a `proc` body. M2 captures the module-level form into
// `ModuleBlock::procs_` (where the printer emits `(StateDefn …)`). The
// proc-body-nested form requires a parallel-block item slot that admits
// Decls; per the M2 simplification recorded in `lib/Parse/ParseStmt.cpp`
// header lines 24–34, internal/decl items inside parallel blocks are
// dropped on the floor at this milestone. Promotion of the proc-nested
// form into the printable AST is therefore deferred to a later
// milestone alongside the same `seq`-block-internal-decl widening.
//
// This fixture exercises the module-level form, which the spec
// authoritatively permits.

